# Agent-agnostic skill paths

Skills and vendor packs live under a **configurable root**. Defaults:

| Environment | Default `AGENT_SKILLS_ROOT` |
|-------------|---------------------------|
| **ai-resources** (this repo) | `$AGENT_KIT/cursor/skills` (`AGENT_KIT` = repo root) |
| Claude Code | `~/.claude/skills` (typical) |
| Custom | `$AGENT_SKILLS_ROOT` if set |

## Layout

- **First-party skills:** `{root}/<category>/<skill>/SKILL.md` (e.g. `common/common-tdd/SKILL.md`).
- **Gentleman-Programming (vendor):** `{root}/vendor/gentleman-programming/curated/<name>/SKILL.md` or `…/community/<name>/SKILL.md`.
- **Shared references:** `{root}/_shared/*.md` (Engram / persistence excerpts).

## Install (any agent)

1. Add **`ai-resources/bin`** to `PATH` and run **`agent-kit self-update`** (or `agent-kit vendor-sync` + `agent-kit generate`).
2. **`agent-kit setup <cursor|claude|…>`** writes short bootstrap files for that IDE.
3. Point the agent’s index (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, etc.) at **`$AGENT_KIT/cursor/skills-registry.md`**, **`$AGENT_KIT/cursor/skills-index.json`**, and/or **`$AGENT_KIT/cursor/AGENTS.md`**.

## ID → path (delegation)

- `vendor/gentleman-programming/curated/typescript` → `{root}/vendor/gentleman-programming/curated/typescript/SKILL.md`
- No slash → `{root}/{id}/SKILL.md`

See `050-subagent-delegation.mdc` for resolution rules in Cursor.
